fields.caption: Tyrell Ringing Shield, left, with her partner of 16 years, Stacy Stewart, said Nebraska should not renew the liquor licenses for the stores in Whiteclay, Neb.
Graffiti in Whiteclay urging alcohol consumers to free their spirit.
Rosie Freier, left, the owner of the Singing Horse Trading Post, and Allyssa Comer, at Freier's store on the Pine Ridge Indian Reservation.
A two-lane highway carries travelers to Whiteclay from the Pine Ridge Indian Reservation, which is across the state line in South Dakota and forbids alcohol.
